gomodel:SYNGO_2443  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Use of a well-documented specific blocker of this type of voltage gated calcium channel reduces evoked inhibitory postsynaptic currents and increased paired pulse ratios, implying a presynaptic origin.\n\n8/2/2018 Pim\n- The effect on Ca2+ is not shown directly in these experiments. However, CACNA1E is a known VGCC. The presynaptic action of CACNA1E inhibitor on ca2+-dependent SV release implies that CACNA1E is involved in 'voltage-gated calcium channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic cytosolic calcium levels (GO:0099626)'.. Experimental description: Methods: Most experiments were done on transverse rat brain slices taken through the middle anterior portion of the nRT" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-22" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2443" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

